  useSupabaseUser  Once logged in, you can   auto-import  your user everywhere inside your vue files.      <  script     setup  >
   const     user     =     useSupabaseUser  ()
   </  script  >  Auth middleware  You can protect your authenticated routes by creating a custom middleware in your project, here is an example:      export     default     defineNuxtRouteMiddleware  ((  to  ,   _from  )   =>   {
       const     user     =     useSupabaseUser  ()

       if   (  !  user.value) {
         return     navigateTo  (  '/login'  )
     }
   })  Then you can reference your middleware in your page with:      definePageMeta  ({
     middleware:   'auth'
   })  Learn more about   Nuxt middleware  and   definePageMeta .  .dark .ct-948368{color:#E1E4E8;}
