  serverSupabaseClient   This section assumes you're familiar with   Nitro , the server engine powered by Nuxt.  This function is working similary as the   useSupabaseClient  composable but is designed to be used in   server routes .  Define your server route and just import the   serverSupabaseClient  from   #supabase/server . Be careful,    serverSupabaseClient  is returning a promise.      import   { serverSupabaseClient }   from     '#supabase/server'

   export     default     eventHandler  (  async   (  event  )   =>   {
       const     client     =     await     serverSupabaseClient  (event)

       const   {   data   }   =     await   client.  from  (  'libraries'  ).  select  (  '*'  )

       return   { libraries: data }
   })  Then call your API route from any vue file:      const     fetchLibrary     =     async   ()   =>   {
       const   {   libraries   }   =     await     $fetch  (  '/api/libraries'  )
   }  Be careful, if you want to call this route on SSR, please read this   section , you must send your browser cookies including your supabase token.      const   {   data  : {   libraries   }}   =     await     useFetch  (  '/api/libraries'  , {
     headers:   useRequestHeaders  ([  'cookie'  ])
   })  .dark .ct-135336{color:#F97583;}
