  serverSupabaseServiceRole   This section assumes you're familiar with   Nitro , the server engine powered by Nuxt.  This function is designed to work only in   server routes , there is no vue composable equivalent.  It works similary as the   serverSupabaseClient  but it provides a client with super admin rights that can bypass your   Row Level Security .   The client is initialized with the   SUPABASE_SERVICE_KEY  you must have in your   .env  file. Checkout the doc if you want to know more about   Supabase keys .  Define your server route and just import the   serverSupabaseServiceRole  from   #supabase/server .      import   { serverSupabaseServiceRole }   from     '#supabase/server'

   export     default     eventHandler  (  async   (  event  )   =>   {
       const     client     =     serverSupabaseServiceRole  (event)

       const   {   data   }   =     await   client.  from  (  'rls-protected-table'  ).  select  ()

       return   { sensitiveData: data }
   })  Then call your API route from any vue file:      const     fetchSensitiveData     =     async   ()   =>   {
       const   {   sensitiveData   }   =     await     useFetch  (  '/api/bypass-rls'  )
   }  .dark .ct-135336{color:#F97583;}
