  serverSupabaseUser   This section assumes you're familiar with   Nitro , the server engine powered by Nuxt.  This function is similar to the   useSupabaseUser  composable but is used in   server routes .  Define your server route and import the   serverSupabaseUser  from   #supabase/server .      import   { serverSupabaseUser }   from     '#supabase/server'

   export     default     defineEventHandler  (  async   (  event  )   =>   {
       return     await     serverSupabaseUser  (event)
   })  Then call your api route from any vue file:      const     user     =     ref  (  null  )

   const     fetchMe     =     async   ()   =>   {
      user.value   =     await     $fetch  (  '/api/me'  )
   }  Be careful, if you want to call this route on SSR, please read this   section , you must send your browser cookies including your supabase token.      const     user     =     ref  (  null  )

   const   {   data   }   =     await     useFetch  (  '/api/me'  , {
     headers:   useRequestHeaders  ([  'cookie'  ])
   })

   user.value   =   data  .dark .ct-135336{color:#F97583;}
